Create Your Partner Telephony Contact Center

After installing your partner telephony provider's managed package from App Exchange, you can create your Service Cloud Voice contact center. You may need to create an XML contact center definition file and import it into Voice.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To view the Partner Telephony Setup page: Customize Application
To view the Partner Telephony Contact Centers page: Customize Application AND Manage Call Centers
To create and manage a contact center: Contact Center Admin (Partner Telephony)

Before you start, ask your telephony provider for the public key. You can add it to the contact center by either:

* Copying and pasting it into a contact center definition file or
* Adding it on the contact center's details page after creation

The public key is required to make and receive calls using Voice.

If your partner telephony provider requires a contact center definition file, you can download a sample file from the Service Cloud Voice Github repository. Customize it for your contact center, save it as an XML file, and copy and paste the public key into it.

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Partner Telephony Setup, then select Partner Telephony Setup. Click Create Contact Center, select your partner telephony provider, and complete the details required by your telephony provider. Check that your contact center is shown in the Contact Centers list view.

Now that you've created your contact center, it's time to configure it. For example, add agents to the contact center, set up your phone channel, and set up agents' and supervisors' workspaces.
title: Setting Up Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony
